I"£l<p>After setting up the pagination, the next thing I wanted to add to my blog was a â€˜properâ€™ archive by both date and category rather than just the reverse chronological list of posts. Although this wasnâ€™t as straightforward as setting up pagination, a bit of searching turned up some sites that helped me get everything running.</p>

<h2 id="archive-by-date">Archive by date</h2>
<p>Because a list of posts in reverse chronological order can be readily accessed in Jekyll through <code class="language-plaintext highlighter-rouge">site.posts</code>, all thatâ€™s needed is to use some clever Liquid markup to process it. 
I used below code to group my archives by year.</p>

